<h3><span lang=3DEN-GB style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-GB;mso-no-proof:yes'>I=
ntelligence
Agents<o:p></o:p></span></h3>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-NZ style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-NZ'>T=
hese
characters have a variety of special missions. By default, they are assigne=
d to
Counter-Intelligence, which helps protect your empire against enemy
Intelligence Agents. See the topic &#8220;Intelligence Missions&#8221; for =
more
information.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<h3><span lang=3DEN-NZ style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-NZ'>Ship Captains<o:p>=
</o:p></span></h3>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-NZ style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-NZ'>A=
 Ship
Captain commands a single starship, providing bonuses to his ship. Ship
Captains often appear spontaneously in pirate factions. They may specialize=
 as
smugglers or bounty hunters.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<h2><span lang=3DEN-GB style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-GB;mso-no-proof:yes'>C=
haracter
Survival<o:p></o:p></span></h2>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-NZ style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-NZ'>C=
haracters
can retire or perish due to a variety of causes. Keep your most valuable
characters safe by making sure that they and the locations where they are
assigned are protected from harm.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-NZ style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-NZ'>C=
haracters
may also be dismissed by using the Dismiss button on the Character Screen, =
but
it may be some time before another character of the same type is generated.=
 In
most cases, it&#8217;s worth trying to develop the characters rather than
dismissing them and hoping a more exceptional character comes along.<o:p></=
o:p></span></p>

<h2><span lang=3DEN-NZ style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-NZ'>New Character Gene=
ration<o:p></o:p></span></h2>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-NZ style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-NZ'>T=
he
player&#8217;s actions influence what kind of new characters are most likel=
y to
be generated. Embarking on a major expansion of military ships is likely to
generate a new Admiral. Similarly, convincing alien factions to sign new
treaties may generate an Ambassador and a critical Research breakthrough may
reveal a new Scientist.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-GB style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-GB;ms=
o-no-proof:
yes'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>

</div>

</body>

</html>

